<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFFCFFC3FF71FF69FE4DFE03" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFCFFC3FF71FF69FDA2FF7B" blockId="20.[151,1437,150,429]" box="[151,607,187,213]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFFCFFC3FF79FF69FF05FF7B" box="[159,248,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="67.[151,250,1945,1969]" captionTargetBox="[193,1394,196,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-19@67.[184,1403,181,1922]" captionTargetPageId="67" captionText="FIGURE 14. Southeast Asian Eudocima and Eudocima tyrannus group adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605535/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs 14</figureCitation>
: E–F, 21: C, 26: O, 32: F, 93: F)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFFCFFC3FF71FF0DFE4DFE03" blockId="20.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
The marginal band on the hindwing is larger than in 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFCFFC3FD16FF0DFC8DFF56" baseAuthorityName="Banziger &amp; Honey" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[752,880,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurantia">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFCFFC3FD16FF0DFC8DFF56" box="[752,880,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">E. aurantia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but barely reaches the wing margin if at all. The background color of the sharply pointed forewing is brownish rather than the variable green shading of 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFCFFC3FAF7FED1FF48FEEE" baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1895" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sikhimensis">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFCFFC3FAF7FED1FF48FEEE" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">E. sikhimensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFCFFC3FE3DFEF5FDB9FEEF" baseAuthorityName="Okano" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[475,580,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="okurai">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFCFFC3FE3DFEF5FDB9FEEF" box="[475,580,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">E. okurai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the shape of the oblique line as discussed under that species. Individuals from the northern portion of the range in Amur and 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFCFFC3FD05FE99FCDEFECB" box="[739,803,331,357]" name="Japan" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Japan</collectingCountry>
show a larger comma-shaped medial patch on the hindwing than in its southern range from 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFCFFC3FDD5FEBDFD84FE27" box="[563,633,367,393]" name="Nepal" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Nepal</collectingCountry>
, Sichuan, 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFCFFC3FD0DFEBDFCB7FE27" box="[747,842,367,393]" name="Vietnam" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFFCFFC3FC98FEBDFC2DFE27" box="[894,976,367,393]" name="Taiwan" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
where it has a smaller patch similar to 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFFCFFC3FA62FEBDFE51FE03" authority="(Zilli et al. 2017)" baseAuthorityName="Zilli" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="okurai">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFCFFC3FA62FEBDFF1DFE03" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">E. okurai</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFFCFFC3FF09FE41FE59FE03" author="Zilli, A. &amp; Brou, V. A. &amp; Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J." box="[239,420,403,429]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="152 - 166" refId="ref41849" refString="Zilli, A., Brou, V. A., Klem, C. &amp; Zaspel, J. (2017) The Eudocima Billberg, 1820 of the Australian Region (Lepidoptera: Erebidae). In: Telnov, D. (Ed.), Biodiversity, Biogeography and Nature Conservation in Wallacea and New Guinea. Vol. 3. The Entomological Society of Latvia, Riga, pp. 631 - 655, pls. 152 - 166." type="book chapter" year="2017">
Zilli 
<emphasis id="579E2338FFFCFFC3FECEFE41FEA4FE03" box="[296,345,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
